	<h4>Freshdesk Raises $31 Million for Customer Support Software</h4>
<p>Big investors are betting that a young rival, Freshdesk, whose software helps companies with customer support, can grow into a dominant firm in its own right.</p>
<p>Freshdesk is expected to announce on Thursday that it has raised $31 million from three investment firms including Google Capital, which manages money for the software giant. The financing round is being led by Tiger Global Management, which is returning after investing earlier, and includes the venture capital firm Accel Partners, also a repeat investor.</p>
<p><a href="http://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/06/12/freshdesk-raises-31-million-for-customer-support-software/" target="_blank">Continue Reading</a></p></div>



<div class="press-item" id='june-2014'>
