	<h4>Girish: CEOs Doing Time on the Support Desk</h4>
<p>As small business owners build their businesses up, add new people and take on more responsibilities, it’s easy to become disconnected from the very folks spurring that growth – their customers. But customer needs and expectations change over time which makes it critically important for the CEO of a growing company to find ways to stay in tune with the voice of the customer.</p>
<p>Girish Mathrubootham, CEO and founder of online customer support platform Freshdesk, came up with the idea of having CEOs dedicate some of their time playing the role of a customer support agent in order to help them stay within ear shot of what’s on the mind of their customers. He discusses what he calls CEO on Support, and the impact it can have on customer relationships.</p>
