	<h3>The report of my death was an exaggeration, Freshdesk tells Forbes &amp; Microsoft</h3>
<p>Cash-rich companies like Microsoft have an easy way to get new ideas and talent: acquire smaller, more innovative companies. But when a big company acquires a startup, what happens to other startups in the space? According to an article in Forbes, that’s the end of competition in that domain, and the other small players might as well shut shop.</p>
<p>Such a tall claim made in an international US-based business publication may have normally gone unchallenged, and misled readers around the world, not to mention clients of all the companies concerned. Freshdesk's CEO Girish Mathrubootham has made it clear that the game was far from being up.</p>
